Show HN: Databoutique.com, a Marketplace for Web Data
text:
Hi all! We’re building a marketplace for web data (https://www.databoutique.com).

If you need web data for training models or app development, you can ask the community for it. The goal is to save time and cut down on scraping costs.

The basic idea is that most of the times, you’ll need data that someone is already scraping, so it’s faster and easier to ask for it, instead of doing again the scrape yourself.

We’re in early phase, any feedback is welcome. We hope this helps lower the barriers to data.

Ask HN: Why would a company ban ChatGPT?
text: I work for a large corporation, that I don't feel comfortable naming, but they sent out an email to all 160K employees forbidding anyone from using Bing, any ChatGPT, GPT of any kind on company computers for security reasons. They provided no explanation other than saying "for security reasons". Does anyone have any idea what it is they are worried about? I don’t see where it could be an issue. How would it be any less secure than a regular search engine?

Show HN: SaaSHub Experts
text:
Hey fellow makers!

I'd like to introduce SaaSHub Experts here.

This is my Nth attempt to organize an active community around promoting software products. I'd describe SaaSHub Experts as an ongoing product tournament.

Why a tournament? Because every workday, the community selects the "Top 5 products of the day" (out of 15). Then, the results are aggregated every week by taking the Top 3 products and nominating them for "Product of the Week". And we have Product of the Month & Year similarly.

Why experts? Product owners and marketers grow their "Expert Rating" by selecting the Top 5 products. You have to choose the Top products according to the community. The more community-matching your selection is, the more points you get. With that in place, new users start with minimal influence and can only influence the result a little. This resolves the issue when someone invites people to register and vote for them.

Who's the top competitor? I think that it is Product Hunt. My goal for SaaSHub Experts is to be the more objective version of Product Hunt. I.e. the best products should be featured instead of the products with the biggest following (as it is on PH).

Why would I want to take part? Every expert can set a product on focus to be featured on their profile and on the homepage of SaaSHub (as a nomination). You will have fun (I hope). You could consider it as a game for product makers as well.

Please let me know what you think. Let's have fun together - promoting the best on the net.

Cheers!

- https://www.saashub.com/experts/about
